T*
() Tj
T*
(Example interpretation: a single repeated query is not enough to prove bot) Tj
T*
(traffic. It becomes more concerning when it appears with a repeated clicked) Tj
T*
(domain, dense same-second activity, reused time-to-click values, or a narrow) Tj
T*
(region/browser/OS footprint.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The new concentrated ct rule is deliberately cautious. It adds low-weight) Tj
T*
(support only when country-like concentration appears with repeated query) Tj
T*
(behaviour and either a heavy device cluster or a same-second burst. Country-like) Tj
T*
(concentration alone is not treated as bot evidence because legitimate campaigns) Tj
T*
(can be country-specific.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 4. Classifier Details) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The rules layer currently scores:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- repeated query/domain pairs) Tj
T*
(- repeated queries) Tj
T*
(- confirmed query repetition) Tj
T*
(- high-volume clicked domains) Tj
T*
(- dense region/browser/OS clusters) Tj
T*
(- exact time-to-click reuse) Tj
T*
(- same-second bursts) Tj
T*
(- dense burst repetition clusters) Tj
T*
(- concentrated ct context paired with repetition and clustering) Tj
T*
(- implausibly fast clicks) Tj
T*
(- moderately long or extreme time-to-click values) Tj
T*
(- regular pseudo-session inter-arrival timing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The exact time-to-click reuse rule uses a 99th-percentile reuse-count threshold) Tj
T*
(with an absolute floor. This lets the rule adapt to the observed timer reuse in) Tj
T*
(the batch while avoiding weak duplicate counts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The ct rule, confirmed query repetition, and dense burst repetition rules are) Tj
T*
(conjunctive. In practical terms, they require multiple signals to be present) Tj
T*
ET
