() Tj
T*
( 6. Method Agreement And Disagreement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Agreement between the rules layer and the anomaly model is useful review) Tj
T*
(evidence. It is not statistical validation, because there are no labels.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(At the ML agreement threshold, this run has 1,478 Heuristic + ML events and 2,253 ML) Tj
T*
(only events.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Method disagreement \(ml_score >= 0.975\):) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Heuristic + ML: 1,478 events) Tj
T*
(- Heuristic only: 612 events) Tj
T*
(- ML only: 2,253 events) Tj
T*
(- Neither strong: 144,896 events) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example interpretation:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Heuristic + ML events are usually the strongest review candidates.) Tj
T*
(- Heuristic only events may be explainable rule hits that are not unusual in) Tj
T*
(  the wider feature space.) Tj
T*
(- ML only events may contain multivariate anomalies, but they need careful) Tj
T*
(  review because unusual legitimate behaviour can also be anomalous.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 7. Operational Actions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter separates prediction from action by assigning operational tiers:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- suppress: 1,966 events) Tj
T*
(- quarantine: 1,765 events) Tj
T*
(- monitor: 145,508 events) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Recommended use:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- suppress: high-confidence traffic that can be excluded from billing or) Tj
T*
(  downstream metrics after policy approval.) Tj
T*
(- quarantine: suspicious traffic that should be reviewed, sampled, or delayed) Tj
T*
(  before suppression.) Tj
T*
(- monitor: traffic not selected for bot action, retained for trend analysis) Tj
T*
(  and future labels.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The binary is_bot field is the compatibility output. The tier is the safer) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
