(business-control layer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 8. Probability Perspective) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The estimated probability that a flagged event is fraudulent is 73%. This is an) Tj
T*
(operational estimate based on signal agreement, not a calibrated probability.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The estimate is stronger when independent signals agree. For example, a click) Tj
T*
(with repeated query/domain replay, same-second burst evidence, and an upper-tail) Tj
T*
(ML score is more likely to be fraudulent than a click selected only because one) Tj
T*
(feature is unusual.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The estimate is weaker for isolated ML-only events, because unsupervised anomaly) Tj
T*
(detection can also surface legitimate edge cases such as unusual campaigns,) Tj
T*
(regional spikes, testing traffic, or rare but valid user behaviour.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 9. Generalisation And Trade-Offs) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The approach should generalise when bot traffic is repetitive, mechanically) Tj
T*
(timed, or concentrated in narrow device and query patterns. It may miss bots) Tj
T*
(that deliberately randomise timing, distribute across many query/domain pairs,) Tj
T*
(or imitate human behaviour closely.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main trade-off is explainability versus coverage. Rules are easier to) Tj
T*
(defend but can miss novel patterns. The anomaly model broadens coverage but) Tj
T*
(needs careful interpretation because it finds unusual events, not necessarily) Tj
T*
(fraudulent events.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Material changes in geography, campaign volume, inventory, browser mix, or) Tj
T*
(feature extraction should trigger fresh threshold review.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 10. Known Limitations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- There are no ground-truth labels, so measured precision, recall, and) Tj
T*
(  calibration cannot be reported.) Tj
T*
(- Legitimate campaigns can create high repetition, dense clusters, or regional) Tj
T*
(  concentration.) Tj
T*
(- The ct rule is supporting evidence only; it should not be used as a) Tj
T*
(  country-level blocking rule.) Tj
T*
(- The regular inter-arrival rule uses pseudo-session groups because there is no) Tj
T*
(  explicit user or session identifier.) Tj
T*
(- The anomaly score is relative to the current batch and should be monitored) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
